reviewText: This was not very well made. I was glad I rented this one rather than bought it.  It was not in depth, but even in the short section on Ida B Well for instance it would use the same footage or picture again.  They are not high quality.  Narration changes,poor graphics on the credits, it is just a B production. Some A+ documentaries on Black history are Roots of Resistance, Africans in America, Citizen King, Murder of Emmett Till, Eyes on the Prize, Slavery by another Name...
